WASHINGTON, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Multiple people, including a police officer, were injured Sunday in a shooting incident in downtown Washington, D.C., local police said. The Metropolitan Police Department tweeted that officers are responding to "the area of 14th and U Street, NW, for a shooting incident." Metropolitan Police Chief Robert Contee will provide a media briefing, the tweet added. The officer who was shot is reportedly hospitalized in stable condition.  â– 